## Development Philosophy

`__PROJECT_NAME__` treats Knowledge-Based Product Development (KBPD) as a
first-class part of the engineering workflow.

Agents should assume:

- decisions are stronger when the knowledge gap is named first
- experiments, failures, trade-offs, and limits should be captured as reusable
  knowledge
- structured knowledge belongs in `.kbriefs/`, not only in chat or commit
  history
- documentation should evolve alongside the code and the knowledge base

